12
00:01:37,271 --> 00:01:40,240
Collect
Sean Michaels.

13
00:01:40,274 --> 00:01:42,435
[Demon roaring]

14
00:01:51,419 --> 00:01:52,386
No!

15
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:54,388
[Screams]

16
00:01:57,391 --> 00:02:00,360
[Demon shrieks]

17
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:29,289
[Haunting piano music]

18
00:02:29,323 --> 00:02:37,287
# #

19
00:03:55,376 --> 00:03:58,311
[wind chimes ringing]

20
00:04:05,519 --> 00:04:07,453
Sean?

21
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:19,399
[Papers rustling]

22
00:04:24,505 --> 00:04:27,440
Where are you?

23
00:05:01,309 --> 00:05:04,301
You left me hanging here.

24
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:09,544
[Sobbing]

25
00:05:10,251 --> 00:05:12,219
Oh, my baby.

26
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:18,358
Helen?

27
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:21,325
Helen?

28
00:05:23,297 --> 00:05:25,288
You were
sleepwalking again.

29
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,493
Why didn't you wake me up
when we got here?

30
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:28,263
I wanted to let you rest.

31
00:05:28,302 --> 00:05:30,327
But you said.

32
00:05:30,371 --> 00:05:31,429
The kids
have been a big help.

33
00:05:31,472 --> 00:05:33,497
We've got most everything
packed already.

34
00:05:55,296 --> 00:05:57,355
I'm gonna
go check on the kids.

35
00:06:09,343 --> 00:06:12,437
Pete, you want to...
you want to take a break?

36
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:15,347
I just want to get...
just get it over with.

37
00:06:15,383 --> 00:06:17,510
Are we separating
Grandpa's stuff from Sean's?

38
00:06:17,518 --> 00:06:20,282
That would be nice.

39
00:06:20,321 --> 00:06:23,347
Can I get you
something to drink?

40
00:06:23,391 --> 00:06:26,417
Not right now, Mom.
Thanks, though.

41
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:34,458
You can, um,
you can stay at home tonight

42
00:06:34,468 --> 00:06:36,368
