the coroner
and the police agreed

51
00:07:44,271 --> 00:07:47,240
that it was self-inflicted,
but I...

52
00:07:47,308 --> 00:07:48,400
What'd you expect?

53
00:07:48,442 --> 00:07:51,309
I mean, he was supposed to be
fixing this house up.

54
00:07:51,345 --> 00:07:52,471
And there's black paint
everywhere,

55
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:54,481
and the mirrors are broken,
and the furniture is...

56
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:56,506
But there has to be
a better explanation.

57
00:07:56,550 --> 00:07:58,484
He was not suicidal.

58
00:07:58,486 --> 00:08:00,454
Can we just change
the subject?

59
00:08:02,523 --> 00:08:04,252
Sorry.

60
00:08:04,291 --> 00:08:05,383
You haven't talked
to your friends

61
00:08:05,392 --> 00:08:06,450
in a really long time.

62
00:08:06,494 --> 00:08:08,462
When's the last time
you talked to Jeanette?

63
00:08:28,249 --> 00:08:32,413
She tried to relate by talking
to me about her dead cat.

64
00:08:32,453 --> 00:08:34,353
You could try meeting
new kids at school.

65
00:08:34,388 --> 00:08:35,355
How about that?

66
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:37,414
You know,
you could go to a club.

67
00:08:37,458 --> 00:08:40,427
You could do drama club.

68
00:08:40,462 --> 00:08:41,394
Join the theater.

69
00:08:41,428 --> 00:08:43,396
You know,
Sean loved the theater.

70
00:08:45,332 --> 00:08:48,301
[Tense music]

71
00:08:48,335 --> 00:08:56,435
# #

72
00:08:56,443 --> 00:08:57,501
[sparks crackling]

73
00:08:57,545 --> 00:08:59,410
Fuck, Sean.

74
00:09:04,385 --> 00:09:06,353
Pete?

75
00:09:10,491 --> 00:09:13,460
[Water running]

76
00:09:32,379 --> 00:09:34,244
[Coughs]

77
00:09:34,315 --> 00:09:35,304
[Knock at door]

78
00:09:35,349 --> 00:09:37,317
Are you okay?

79
00:09:38,485 --> 00:09:41,454
Uh, yeah.
I'm... I'm fine.

80
00:09:41,488 --> 00:09:44,389
Just... just a little sick
to my stomach.

81
00:09:49,430 --> 00:09:52,399
Uh, Mom?

82
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:54,298
Can I talk to you
about something?

83
00:09:58,405 --> 00:10:01,238
Let's talk when you
come out of the bathroom.

84
00:10:04,278 --> 00:10:05,506
Never mind.

85
00:10:14,521 --> 00:10:16,386
We don't have to sell
the house.

86
00:10:16,423 --> 00:10:18,323
I mean, we've always
managed before.

87
00:10:18,359 --> 00:10:20,293
It would've fixed up
real nice,

88
00:10:20,294 --> 00:10:22,353
just the way
Sean wanted it.

89
00:10:37,244 --> 00:10:39,303
[School bell rings]

90
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:49,414
Tomorrow and tomorrow
and tomorrow,

91
00:10:49,456 --> 00:10:52,357
creeps in this petty pace
from day to day

92
00:10:52,393 --> 00:10:55,226
to the last syllable
of recorded time.

93
00:10:55,262 --> 00:10:56,320
And all our yesterdays

94
00:10:56,363 --> 00:10:59,298
have lighted fools their way
to dusty death.

95
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:02,393
Out, out, brief candle.

96
00:11:02,403 --> 00:11:07,238
Life is but
a walking shadow.

97
00:11:07,274 --> 00:11:09,401
You know
he's going to get lead.

98
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:11,275
I wouldn't mind
starring with him.

99
00:11:11,311 --> 00:11:13,438
It is a tale
told by an idiot,

100
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:18,315
full of sound and fury,
signifying nothing.

101
00:11:21,488 --> 00:11:22,455
Scene.

102
00:11:22,489 --> 00:11:25,322
[Applause]

103
00:11:26,427 --> 00:11:27,485
Whoo!

104
00:11:35,536 --> 00:11:37,333
Kathryn?

105
00:11:42,543 --> 00:11:44,408
[Girls giggling]

106
00:11:44,411 --> 00:11:47,244
Kathryn Michaels?

107
00:12:00,427 --> 00:12:02,361
My name is Kate Michaels,

108
00:12:02,362 --> 00:12:05,297
and I will be doing
a piece that I wrote.

109
00:12:05,332 --> 00:12:06,356
Is that all right?

110
00:12:06,366 --> 00:12:07,458
Proceed.

111
00:12:17,444 --> 00:12:20,345
Dear God,

112
00:12:20,414 --> 00:12:23,247
I heard that you can see
into people's hearts,

113
00:12:23,283 --> 00:12:25,410
and I wonder
what you find,

114
00:12:25,452 --> 00:12:29,252
because everybody I know
wears the same face.

115
00:12:29,289 --> 00:12:32,258
They carve their thoughts
into bite-size pieces

116
00:12:32,292 --> 00:12:36,524
and hack their emotions
down to a manageable size

117
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:39,431
till their words are dulled
to travel down their tongues.

118
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:43,267
I would ask you to shatter
their grotesque masks

119
00:12:43,303 --> 00:12:44,497
and let me see
what's within.

120
00:12:44,538 --> 00:12:48,406
But I fear finding nothing,

121
00:12:48,442 --> 00:12:52,401
that my thoughts
would choke them,

122
00:12:52,446 --> 00:12:54,277
and my feelings
crush them,

123
00:12:54,314 --> 00:12:57,283
and my words
slice their tongues.

124
00:12:57,317 --> 00:13:00,411
So you remain quiet,

125
00:13:00,454 --> 00:13:03,514
and I'll pretend
that they' re hiding.

126
00:13:04,258 --> 00:13:05,384
You remain quiet,

127
00:13:05,392 --> 00:13:08,452
and I'll pretend
that you' re there.

128
00:13:08,495 --> 00:13:10,463
Scene.

129
00:13:14,334 --> 00:13:15,301
Awesome.

130
00:13:15,335 --> 00:13:19,294
Ooh, thank you so much.

131
00:13:19,339 --> 00:13:21,239
Okay, bye.

132
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:25,344
[Clears throat]

133
00:13:25,379 --> 00:13:28,246
Bless us, O Lord,
for these Thy gifts

134
00:13:28,282 --> 00:13:30,375
which we are about to receive
from your bounty

135
00:13:30,417 --> 00:13:33,352
through Christ our Lord,
amen.

136
00:13:33,353 --> 00:13:35,321
Amen.

137
00:13:35,355 --> 00:13:36,413
So who was on the phone?

138
00:13:36,456 --> 00:13:38,253
That was Miss Bliss.

139
00:13:38,292 --> 00:13:39,259
Who?

140
00:13:39,326 --> 00:13:40,452
Miss Bliss,
my theater teacher.

141
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:42,257
She said that
all the other girls

142
00:13:42,329 --> 00:13:43,353
were more experienced.

143
00:13:43,363 --> 00:13:45,388
[Clears throat]
I'll get them.

144
00:13:45,432 --> 00:13:48,424
But she's giving me
the leading role.

145
00:13:48,435 --> 00:13:49,402
Really?

146
00:13:49,436 --> 00:13:50,403
Yeah.

147
00:13:50,470 --> 00:13:52,404
That's fantastic.

148
00:13:52,406 --> 00:13:53,373
What for?

149
00:13:53,407 --> 00:13:55,375
[Scoffs]
The winter play, Dad.

150
00:14:01,348 --> 00:14:02,372
Well,
I want to hear more,

151
00:14:02,416 --> 00:14:05,249
but I have something
that we need to talk about.

152
00:14:06,386 --> 00:14:09,446
I found something disturbing
at Sean's grave today.

153
00:14:09,456 --> 00:14:11,321
What?

154
00:14:14,461 --> 00:14:18,227
[Crows cawing]

155
00:14:18,265 --> 00:14:22,326
A dead raven nailed to the
ground next to his headstone.

156
00:14:25,305 --> 00:14:28,468
And there was this...
this woman.

157
00:14:33,413 --> 00:14:35,438
What was she doing?

158
00:14:38,285 --> 00:14:39,343
I don't know.

159
00:14:50,497 --> 00:14:53,261
Exactly.

160
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:55,427
Mom's in denial
about Sean's suicide.

161
00:14:55,435 --> 00:14:57,300
Sean was a mess
before he died,

162
00:14:57,337 --> 00:15:00,238
completely paranoid
and delusional.

163
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:02,333
He wired pipe bombs
in his closet.

164
00:15:02,376 --> 00:15:03,365
Why?

165
00:15:03,410 --> 00:15:06,470
I think to protect
his notebooks.

166
00:15:06,513 --> 00:15:08,378
Have you seen them?

167
00:15:08,415 --> 00:15:11,316
[Tree branches creaking]

168
00:15:17,557 --> 00:15:20,287
[Dog howling]

169
00:15:37,277 --> 00:15:40,269
I don't know.
This is really...

170
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,248
This is just...

171
00:15:42,282 --> 00:15:44,341
This house is...

172
00:15:44,384 --> 00:15:46,352
I don't know either.

173
00:15:48,388 --> 00:15:51,289
Look at this.
What is this?

174
00:15:57,331 --> 00:16:01,267
Bankruptcy,
wedding ads,

175
00:16:01,301 --> 00:16:04,395
mattress sale,
wholesale factory outlet,

176
00:16:04,404 --> 00:16:06,497
tampon ads, used cars.

177
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:08,508
Planned betrayal?

178
00:16:12,446 --> 00:16:15,347
" Cover the reflections,
any reflections. "

179
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:19,410
" He comes for us.

180
00:16:19,453 --> 00:16:22,422
10:28.
10:28."

181
00:16:22,456 --> 00:16:24,424
What?

182
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:29,327
" Black paint...
Worked. "

183
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:45,436
You' re going to stay?

184
00:16:45,479 --> 00:16:47,242
Do I need to stop
at the store?

185
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:50,340
No, there's things
in the freezer.

186
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:52,352
Okay.

187
00:16:52,386 --> 00:16:54,286
Drive careful.

188
00:16:54,321 --> 00:16:56,289
I love ya.

189
00:16:57,391 --> 00:16:59,359
Let's go.

190
00:17:15,442 --> 00:17:18,434
[Clocks ticking]

191
